m not ripping Tal, who led what sounds like a successful XA raid.  I'm not ripping XA, as there are members who weren't even there who seem to be caught in the crossfire.<br><br>I'm concerned that Delta, in effect, pulled an &quot;Inner Circle&quot; move, and completely blew off the other mages that had contributed to clearing Hate to the Magi...especially given his position as leader of XA.<br><br>Have I been heated today in my posts?  Yes.  Have I tried to remain civil?  Yes.  Should I even be posting this here?  No...but I feel compelled as I have all day to find out if the principles I always thought XA stood for are not being displayed by their leadership.<br><br>Delta, I'm simply asking if you seriously completely disregarded the fact that other mages had saved your guild time and effort by intentionally defaulting the staff to yourself and, in effect, telling them to go home?<br><br>I guess I'm too soft hearted, but if I were one of the leaders of XA, and I led a Fear raid 6 months ago, only to reach the time limit before we could engage the Demi's...I'd sure have recognized the efforts of the other SK's there for the previous 4 hours and included them in rolls if they stayed, rather than, in effect, saying &quot;Thanks for doing the dirty work for us.  HKD will take it from here.  Soul Leech defaults to Rukog!&quot;<br><br>That sounds SO Inner Circle...not what I'd expect from a leader of the Xegony Alliance.<br><br>Thank you for allowing me into your home to address this here rather than continue the bickering on the XA board.  I look forward to many civil responses.<br><br>Sincerely,<br><br> <p>Rukog DethBryngr<BR>Troll Grave Lord<BR>Royal Advisor of House Kel'Dar<BR>Xegony<BR><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/udeltanamossumnorxegony.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deltanamos Sumnor Xegony</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="