s to remain on topic, polite, void of name calling and childish behavior, and to the point.  And if you can please don't use the word suxxors or other doodspeak or whatever it's called k thnx!<br><br>Begin XA quote:<br><br>This has been a great read.  Most of you have expressed yourself intelligently and coherantly, and have valid points.  This being said, I am going to post my only response on this forum because my guild is being attacked as being involved in a 'conspiricy.'<br><br>Here are the events as seen through the eyes of myself and the rest of my guild excluding Deltanamos *and let it be said that Delt is not the guildleader of Soul Survivors, and does not command us at will like some of you think*.<br><br>At the time of the XA Hate raid, I was leading a small war raid in Acrylia Caverns.  I had heard word of XA in hate and gave it no more thought, as I am not an XA raider.  I want to stress this fact..Soul Survivors is not an XA affiliated guild.  In fact, I'm constantly telling Delt to pay as much attention and heart to our guild as he does to helping the people in XA.  We *Soul Survivors* have our own agenda's, but two or three of our members are very prominent in XA and we do, overall I believe, respect and admire XA.  During this 'raid' in AC, Delt informs us via guildchat that the Magi Spawned, and that the XA raid was ending due to not having the proper set up to kill the magi, and their time was up as POSTED in the calendar.  As some of you know Delt has been after this piece for a VERY long time and we hear about it a LOT. :)  <br><br>Well when I found out that the magi was up, and XA was not going to kill as they stated in the XA channel, I told Delt that I would call my raid and move it to Hate in a heartbeat if the Magi was up for grabs.  Delt nor myself had given any thought prior, to using XA to clear all the trash just to benefit us.  I in fact had to push Delt into letting me move the raid as he was hesitant to end the guild raid, just to help him.  This is the type of person Delt is....everyone else first. <br><br>Needless to say my raid was in Sro in 5 minutes ready to go up.  I'm in full belief that if House Kel'Dar, or whatever their name is now, cared about their mage, they would have been there too had they known he was up; I would garner he would have told his guild he wanted this piece, and them knowing he was in hate, they might have had their ears pricked up to assist him or congrat him.  I find it hard to believe that in all this time the Magi was up, this mage who was waiting and hoping and praying for him to spawn, and was on this raid to benefit himself in a way his guild would apparently not, had never once seen him cast a spell.  The very minute I entered the plane and went to the camp spot I could see the Magi Casting.<br><br>Now at this point, the XA raid was over.  You can blame me for taking my guild up.... I don't mind in the least cause that's what I do.  This was my guild's raid at this point and I was instructing people on what to do.  Delt invited the XA people who had stayed behind to help us kill Magi.  Mind you we didn't require assistance, but in the process of pulling Magi and his cohorts, there was loot to be had and we didn't mind anyone else to be in on it; and we were happy for the company!<br><br>I'm not here to defend Deltanamos.  I'm not here to defend XA.  I'm here in the defense of my guild who was wrongfully accused of some 'allied subversion.'  Should anyone want to discuss this further, as this is the only thing that need be discussed in my opinion, I invite you all over to our guild message boards where I personlly will start the thread.  http://pub44.ezboard.com/bpremierguildforum  Ok, I just checked and see that a thread has already started under our Main forum so go check it out.  heh<br><br>PS<br>I have my own raid rules as every guild on EQ does.  No one else is to be held responsible for what I allow on my raids.  I was there for my oldest eq friend Deltanamos, and I still see no reason as to why I would end my raid, move to Hate for an epic mob, and allow XA mages to roll just because they had been in the zone prior and were the remnants of an ended raid.  I wouldn't be letting someone from any guild or affiliation roll on epic loot on a mob I kill.  Sorry but that's how eq works.  <br><br>Now let's remember...this is a game and it's intended for fun so get out there and have some!<br><br>end quote<br><br>now on here I WILL defend Deltanamos. <p>Burgh Edin 60 Warlord</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/urukogdethbryngr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rukog DethBryngr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soul Survivor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 7:42:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/image.aspx?path=/CoachK69/fullsize%5cEQ/Troll1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Clearing thread from XA - No need to continue it there</span><hr size=1> I would expect nothing less than defense of a guildmember...which is, in effect, the mode I've been in all day.<br><br>It appears this simply has to be, as Slyde loves to put it, &quot;One of those things we'll have to agree to disagree about.&quot;<br><br>My personal values seem to be different from yours, is all.  Am I now saying you are slime?  No.  At this point, I'm saying my values are DIFFERENT, not better.<br><br>I would never have allowed myself to disregard a couple other SK's in a similar circumstance on a Soul Leech or Hide drop, especially if one of them had asked me why it was being defaulted after they assisted in clearing to the mob for 4 hours.<br><br>Was that your call Delta?  It sounds like Burgh is taking some responsibility.  I 